memberdef.name: NDFileJPEG

briefdescription.para: Constructor for NDFileJPEG; all parameters are simply passed to NDPluginFile::NDPluginFile.

parameterdescription.para: The name of the asyn port driver to be created.

The number of NDArrays that the input queue for this plugin can hold when NDPluginDriverBlockingCallbacks=0. Larger queues can decrease the number of dropped arrays, at the expense of more NDArray buffers being allocated from the underlying driver's NDArrayPool.
Initial setting for the NDPluginDriverBlockingCallbacks flag. 0=callbacks are queued and executed by the callback thread; 1 callbacks execute in the thread of the driver doing the callbacks.
Name of asyn port driver for initial source of NDArray callbacks.
asyn port driver address for initial source of NDArray callbacks.
The thread priority for the asyn port driver thread if ASYN_CANBLOCK is set in asynFlags.
The stack size for the asyn port driver thread if ASYN_CANBLOCK is set in asynFlags.
The name of the file to open.
Mask defining how the file should be opened; bits are NDFileModeRead, NDFileModeWrite, NDFileModeAppend, NDFileModeMultiple
A pointer to an NDArray; this is used to determine the array and attribute properties.

briefdescription.para: Reads single NDArray from a JPEG file; NOT CURRENTLY IMPLEMENTED.

parameterdescription.para: Pointer to the NDArray to be read

briefdescription.para: Writes single NDArray to the JPEG file.

parameterdescription.para: Pointer to the NDArray to be written

briefdescription.para: Initializes the destination file; should be private but called from C so must be public.
Empties the output buffer; should be private but called from C so must be public.
Terminates the destination file; should be private but called from C so must be public.
Writes NDArrays in the JPEG file format, which is a lossy compression format.

detaileddescription.para: This plugin was developed using the libjpeg library to write the file.
